    <briefdescription>
<para>Power / voltage monitor. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Wraps ADC + hysteresis to provide voltage monitoring with brownout detection and recovery callbacks. Optionally pushes readings to a <ref refid="structSYN__Signal" kindref="compound">SYN_Signal</ref> window for noise statistics.</para>
<para>Usage: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/><ref refid="structSYN__Power" kindref="compound">SYN_Power</ref><sp/>pwr;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/><ref refid="structSYN__ADC" kindref="compound">SYN_ADC</ref><sp/><sp/><sp/>vbat_adc;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structSYN__Power__Config" kindref="compound">SYN_Power_Config</ref><sp/>cfg<sp/>=<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.<ref refid="structSYN__Power__Config_1a8fd432673c93f39899bb965ecea660be" kindref="member">adc</ref><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>=<sp/>&amp;vbat_adc,</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.brownout_mv<sp/><sp/><sp/>=<sp/>3000,<sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>3.0V</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.restore_mv<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>=<sp/>3200,<sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>3.2V<sp/>(hysteresis)</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.on_brownout<sp/><sp/><sp/>=<sp/>my_brownout_handler,</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.on_restore<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>=<sp/>my_restore_handler,</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">};</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__power_8c_1a4f911574d6b4499b120155d94a180b51" kindref="member">syn_power_init</ref>(&amp;pwr,<sp/>&amp;cfg);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>In<sp/>your<sp/>main<sp/>loop:</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__power_8c_1a70df7330588ab686cd01278a844b7e9c" kindref="member">syn_power_update</ref>(&amp;pwr);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">int32_t<sp/>mv<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="syn__power_8h_1a37eda02712c3aaf0b3e8815659eaed6f" kindref="member">syn_power_voltage_mv</ref>(&amp;pwr);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
